OL,3,CNumber of pensioners living in poverty
OL,4,Ccould double by 2040, charity warns
OL,6,FIt also has a societal cost, with the
OL,7,Fchoices older people in financial
OL,8,Fhardship are forced to make often
OL,9,Fimpacting their well-being, leading to
OL,10,Fincreased health and social care costs.
OL,12,F79-year-old Yvonne Bailey from Witney,
OL,13,FOxfordshire is concerned for her
OL,14,Ffuture.
OL,16,FShe says she has always been careful
OL,17,Fwith money but her osteoporosis means
OL,18,Fshe needs to be warm and paying the
OL,19,Fbills is a real struggle.
